A '''mining simulator''' is a system used to replicate elements of [[mining]] operations, for [[training]] or efficiency analysis. Mining simulation application can range from pure statistical analysis, to scale models, all the way to replica cabins of mining machinery mounted on [[pneumatic]] actuators surrounded by screens displaying [[3D computer graphics|three-dimensional]] imagery. These simulators rely on [[physics engine]]s and [[geodata]] to accurately simulate the dynamics of the environment.
==See also== *[[Flight simulation]]
